data.content:
The root cause is that .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which has significant breaking changes. Here's what changed and how to fix each piece:

---

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` is gone → use `System.Text.Json.Nodes`

All `IOpenApiAny` types (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc.) were removed. Properties like `Schema.Example` are now `JsonNode?`.

```csharp
// Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// New
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. References use dedicated reference types

Instead of creating an object and setting its `Reference` property, use the new `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References` namespace:

```csharp
// Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// New
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### 3. `Nullable` property removed → use `JsonSchemaType` flags

In OpenAPI 3.1 (which v2 of the library targets), nullability is expressed via the `Type` flags enum, not a separate `Nullable` bool.

```csharp
// Old
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// New
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "..." } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("...")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
